'''Rebel assault armor''' was a type of heavy [[Armor/Legends|armor]] that was used by the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Alliance to Restore the Republic]] during the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]].

==Description==
[[File:RebelAssaultCamo-SWG.jpg|thumb|left|120px|A Rebel Assault Forest Camouflage Armor.]]
The Rebel assault armor was developed for modern combat and was often worn by a soldier needing to retain their agility while ensuring maximum protection against pulse-wave blasters. In fact, it offered a high degree of protection against kinetic damage but lesser protection from energy-based weapons like [[Blaster/Legends|blasters]]. The complete armor set was composed of the helmet, chest plate, left & right biceps, left & right bracers, gloves, leggings and boots. Typical suits had to be [[biolinked]] to the wearer to prevent unwanted use; they were also very expensive to create, meaning that such assault armor was a rare sight in battle.<ref name="SWG:CU" />

A variant of this armor, the '''Rebel assault forest camouflage armor''', was designed to help Rebel assault troops blend with forest environments.<ref name="SWG:RTP">{{SWGcite|exp=NGE|type=other|Rebel Theme Park}}</ref>

Another variant was the '''Rebel Special Ops Officer armor''',<ref name="GCWRaR">{{SonyCite|url=players/content.vm?id=66916&resource=features|text=Galactic Civil War Rank and Rewards}}</ref> best known as the '''Rebel Special Ops armor'''.<ref name="SWG:C3">{{SWGcite|exp=NGE|type=other|Chapter 3: Smugglers and Scoundrels}}</ref> This armor was originally developed for [[Alliance Special Operations/Legends|Special Operations]] [[Officer/Legends|officers]]<ref name="GCWRaR" /> but it was eventually provided to any Alliance [[Soldier/Legends|soldier]] who had reached the [[Military rank/Legends|rank]] of [[Commander/Legends|commander]] by proving superior fighting skills on the battlefield.<ref name="SWG:C3" />

==History==
After the [[Battle of Yavin/Legends|Battle of Yavin]], Rebel assault armor were sometimes used by [[Heavy Weapons Specialists]].<ref name="SWGTCG">{{SWGTCG|set=The Nightsister's Revenge|cardname=Heavy Weapon Specialist}}</ref>

In [[1 ABY/Legends|1 ABY]],<ref name="SWG_timeline">{{SWG_timeline}}</ref> certain [[Spacer/Legends|spacers]] who allied with the Alliance to Restore the Republic received camouflaged Rebel assault armor for serving and assisting certain high-profile Rebellion leaders while they were in hiding within the [[Hidden Rebel Base]] on [[Corellia/Legends|Corellia]].<ref name="SWG:RTP" /> The same year, Rebel assault armor was worn by the Alliance organizer of the [[Remembrance Day]] event on Corellia.<ref name="SWG:ED">{{SWGcite|exp=NGE|type=event|Remembrance Day}}</ref>

Also in 1 ABY,<ref name="SWG_timeline" /> a spacer retrieved the nine parts of a Rebel battle armor while visiting multiple worlds in [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy]] and finally assembled the complete armor.<ref name="SWG:LRAA">{{SWGcite|exp=NGE|type=collection|Lost Rebel Assault Armor}}</ref>

During the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]], the [[Mistryl Assault Trooper]]s used an armor that included an helmet very similar to the Rebel assault armor helmet.<ref name="SWG:C6">{{SWGcite|exp=NGE|type=other|Chapter 6}}</ref>

==Behind the scenes==
The Rebel assault armor appeared in the [[2003]] [[Star Wars video games|video game]] ''[[Star Wars Galaxies]]'', a [[Wikipedia:Massively multiplayer online role-playing game|massively multiplayer online roleplaying game]] developed by [[Sony]] Online Entertainment and published by [[LucasArts]],<ref name="SWG:CU" /> prior to its closure on [[December 15]], [[2011]].<ref name="Shutdown">{{SonyCite|url=playerinfo|text=IMPORTANT INFORMATION ABOUT ''STAR WARS'' GALAXIES™}}</ref> The Rebel assault armor was one of the Rebel [[W:c:swg:Faction armor|faction armors]] added to the game with the release of the "[[W:c:swg:Combat Upgrade|Combat Upgrade]],"<ref name="SonyCite-Combat Upgrade: Armor System">{{SonyCite|url=content.jsp?page=Combat%20Upgrade:%20Armor%20System|text=Combat Upgrade: Armor System}}</ref> on [[April 27]], [[2005]].<ref name="SonyCite-Publish Archive 2005">{{SonyCite|url=players/content.vm?id=64886&resource=publish|text=Publish Archive 2005}}</ref> The Rebel Assault Forest Camouflage Armor was added to the game with the revamped "[[W:c:swg:Rebel Theme Park|Rebel Theme Park]]," released with the "[[W:c:swg:Chapter 6 Notes for May 22 2007|Chapter 6]]" update, on [[May 22]], [[2007]].<ref name="SonyCite-Publish Notes – Chapter 6: Masters of the Wild">{{SonyCite|url=players/news_archive.vm?id=67250&month=052007|text=Publish Notes &ndash; Chapter 6: Masters of the Wild}}</ref>

